        <div class="p-3 mx-3 bg-light br-40 mt-4" id="communityGuid">
            <div class="mb-3 text-center mt-3">
                <h1 class="head5 my-3">SheDrives Community Guidelines</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="text-right"><a href="#pageTop" class="text-grey">Back to top<i class="fa-solid fa-hand-pointer ml-1"></i></a></div>
            <div class="text-left mt-4 terms-text px-3">
                <p>The Community Guidelines were created to ensure that all users of the SheDrives platform experience a secure and respectful environment.
                   These guidelines are integrated into SheDrives' Terms of Use and form part
                   of the agreement between you and SheDrives. They apply to all users of our platform.</p>

                <p>These guidelines encompass rules outlined in our Safety Pact, and any violation may result in losing access to the SheDrives platform.
                   Consistently failing to meet the standards, or breaching rules and principles mentioned in these guidelines, directly undermines the
                   safety and integrity of the SheDrives platform and may lead to SheDrives taking action,
                   including temporarily or permanently suspending your account.</p>

                <h2 class="mt-4 mb-2">Community Guidelines Principles</h2>
                <p>We expect all our users to adhere to the following four principles:</p>
                <p>Complying with the law: We are committed to adhering to all laws and regulations where SheDrives operates, and we expect all
                    users to do the same.</p>
                <p>Delivering quality services: We strive to provide the best service for all users, and we expect all users to act accordingly.</p>
                <p><b>Treating everyone with respect: </b>We promote positive interactions among all users and expect our users to treat each other fairly, with respect and care.</p>
                <p><b>Prioritizing safety: </b>We value safety above all and expect all users to prioritize and support a secure environment.</p>
                <p>When all users of SheDrives abide by these principles, we maintain a quality-focused, healthy, and safe community for everyone, fulfilling our primary commitment to promoting social equity.</p>
                <p>To learn more about the rules, please visit the Safety Pact page on our website.</p>

                <h2 class="mt-4 mb-2">Content-Related Violations</h2>
                <p>Do not share illegal content: We do not permit the posting, sharing, or distribution of content that is illegal, such as materials related to child exploitation, or content that supports, coordinates, or glorifies terrorism and violent acts.</p>
                <p><b>Keep inappropriate content off SheDrives: </b>Do not share or display visuals that are sexually suggestive, such as objects, posters, cartoons, pictures, or drawings. Avoid making graphic comments, lewd remarks, sex-based epithets, obscene comments, derogatory remarks, sexually degrading words, slurs, sexual jokes, innuendo, or unwanted flirtations.
                    Refrain from commenting on an individual's body, sexual prowess, or deficiencies.</p>

                <h2 class="mt-4 mb-2">What Happens if I Violate These Guidelines?</h2>
                <p>If you violate these guidelines, SheDrives may take the following actions:</p>
                <p><b>Warning: </b> You may receive a warning message.</p>
                <p><b>Temporary deactivation of your account: </b>Your access to your account may be temporarily suspended. You will be notified of the reason and duration of the suspension.</p>
                <p><b>Permanent deactivation of your account:</b>Your access to your account may be permanently suspended, and you will no longer be able to use the SheDrives platform.</p>
                <p><b>Incident reports to law enforcement:</b>: SheDrives will cooperate with law enforcement agencies in their investigations and provide all necessary and relevant information.</p>
                <p>When reviewing cases of guideline violations, SheDrives approaches each case individually. Actions taken are based on principles of fairness, ensuring that:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Cases are dealt with promptly and effectively;</li>
                    <li>Users involved are kept informed of the process;</li>
                    <li>Cases are adequately investigated;</li>
                </ul>

                <h2 class="mt-4 mb-2">Appropriate actions are implemented.</h2>
                <p>SheDrives will always notify users if they are at risk of any action. However, there are instances where SheDrives will implement actions without prior warning, such as when an automated suspension system is used, when reports or information require immediate legal or safety review, or when unlawful or fraudulent behavior is detected.</p>
                <p>All actions taken by SheDrives are subject to appeal by users to ensure fairness and protect against unjust or inaccurate reports and complaints.</p>

                <h2 class="mt-4 mb-2">Appeal Process</h2>
                <p>SheDrives uses data and platform information to identify and address safety issues. Users are always given the opportunity to request a human review either before a decision is made or after it is enforced (an appeal). This ensures that users are treated fairly and that their accounts aren’t impacted by fraudulent reports. All actions are subject to appeal by the user.</p>
                <p>It should also be noted that if a user has been affected by an action due to a low rating (3 stars or less) or a series of negative reviews and ratings, they can appeal the decision. The appeal will be reevaluated if the user provides substantial evidence that the low rating and reviews were the result of unsubstantiated reports, including but not limited to discrimination or other reasons unrelated to the user's behavior.</p>
                <p>SheDrives will always inform drivers and clients if they are at risk of any action against them. However, there are occasions when SheDrives will take action against users without prior notice, such as when reports or information necessitate immediate legal or safety review, or when SheDrives determines that a user has engaged in unlawful or fraudulent behavior, as required by applicable laws and regulations.</p>

                <h2 class="mt-4 mb-2">Remediation Option</h2>
                <p>If a user who has allegedly violated these guidelines wishes to rectify the situation, they may do so if both parties involved in the incident agree and communicate with SheDrives. We may then review the case and potentially cancel actions taken against such users.</p>
                <p>Any remediation review will depend on:</p>
                <p>The type of violation;</p>
                <p>Whether the damage done can be repaired;</p>
                <p>A case-by-case analysis.</p>
                <h3>How to Contact Us</h3>
                <p>If you have additional questions, encounter difficulties, or have any feedback regarding these guidelines, please contact us. There are several ways to do so:</p>
                <p>By phone: +92-3417025881;</p>
                <p>By in-app chat: Open the App - Swipe left - Select "Support" - Write a message;</p>
                <p>Via the contact form on our website: SheDrives Support.</p>
                <p>This version is customized for SheDrives while retaining the core concepts and structure of the original document.</p>



            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-3 mx-3 bg-light br-40 mt-4" id="firearmsGuid">
            <div class="mb-3 text-center mt-3">
                <h1 class="head5 my-3">SheDrives Firearms and Weapons Guidelines</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="text-right"><a href="#pageTop" class="text-grey">Back to top<i class="fa-solid fa-hand-pointer ml-1"></i></a></div>
            <div class="text-left mt-4 terms-text px-3">
                <p>Pakistan <br>
                    UG-41 Eden Tower Gulberg 3, Lahore</p>
                <p><b>Creation Date: </b>August 12, 2024,</p>

                <h2 class="mt-4 mb-2">Overview</h2>
                <p>This Firearms and Weapons Guidelines ("Guidelines") are expressly included in reference to SheDrives's Terms of Use and form part of a
                    binding agreement between you and SheDrives XIX of 2017. These Guidelines provide essential information regarding the carriage and usage
                    of firearms and weapons while using SheDrives’s platform (the “App”).</p>
                <p>These Guidelines apply to both passengers and drivers, as well as all other individuals utilizing our services and platform”). Certain sections of these Guidelines may be specifically applicable
                   to either passengers or drivers of the ride-hailing services, as determined by the context.</p>


                <h2 class="mt-4 mb-2">SheDrives Firearms and Weapons Guidelines</h2>
                <p>SheDrives is dedicated to maintaining the safety and comfort of all its Users, including passengers, drivers, and the wider community. In line with this commitment, SheDrives imposes strict regulations on the presence of firearms and other weapons during the use of its service. These Guidelines are designed to comply with local and national laws,
                    upholding the highest standards of safety and legal adherence.</p>

                <h2 class="mt-4 mb-2">Guidelines Summary</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Prohibition of Firearms and Weapons: SheDrives prohibits all Users, including both passengers and drivers, from carrying firearms, any type of weapons, or objects that could be perceived as weapons while using the SheDrives App, except as legally permitted.</li>
                    <li>Transporting Firearms Under Specific Circumstances: In situations where the transportation of firearms is both necessary and legal, Users must strictly follow the protocols set by the Transportation Security Administration (“TSA”) and any applicable federal, state, or local laws related to the transportation of firearms and ammunition.
                        The following conditions must specifically be met:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Firearms must be fully unloaded;</li>
                            <li>Firearms and all firearm components, including but not limited to magazines, clips, bolts, and firing pins, must be secured within a hard-sided, locked container. This container must be placed in the trunk or the most secure compartment of the vehicle; and</li>
                            <li>Ammunition must be stored separately in a portion of the vehicle that is not accessible to the driver or passengers during transit.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><b>Responsibility and Adherence: </b> It is the duty of the User transporting firearms or ammunition to ensure full adherence to these Guidelines and all relevant laws. A lack of knowledge of the Guidelines or applicable laws will not be accepted as a valid justification for non-compliance.</li>
                    <li><b>Consequences of Guideline Violations:</b> Non-compliance with these Guidelines may lead to immediate account deactivation and further actions as deemed necessary by SheDrives, which may include legal action and collaboration with law enforcement.</li>
                    <li><b>Safety and Reporting:</b> SheDrives promotes a culture of safety and vigilance. Users are encouraged to discreetly report any violations of these Guidelines using the SheDrives App's reporting features or by directly contacting SheDrives support. SheDrives is committed to thoroughly investigating all reported incidents and taking appropriate measures to ensure a safe environment for all Users.</li>
                    <li><b>Periodic Review and Revisions:</b>SheDrives reserves the right to periodically review and revise these Guidelines to reflect changes in legal requirements, industry standards, or company practices. Users will be notified of any significant updates to the Guidelines.</li>

                    <p>By using the SheDrives App, all Users acknowledge their understanding of these Firearms and Weapons Guidelines and commit to their strict adherence, ensuring a safe and secure environment for everyone involved.</p>
                    <p><b>Note:</b> These Guidelines are subject to modifications to align with local regulations and legal requirements. Users are responsible for staying informed about the laws in their jurisdictions and complying with the most stringent standards applicable to them</p>
                </ol>

            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-3 mx-3 bg-light br-40 mt-4" id="selfieCheck">
            <div class="mb-3 text-center mt-3">
                <h1 class="head5 my-3">SELFIE CHECKS DATA PRIVACY STATEMENT</h1>
            </div>
